cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY

This paper deals with knowledge representation and natural language processing, which are both sub-fields of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of skip-grams and other linear connectionist models of distributed representation also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses visualization and mapping of data, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and social network analysis (cs.SI). Finally, the use of digital records and behavioral data suggests a connection to cybersecurity (cs.CY).
